All male citizens of this State shall be subject to the performance of military duty,
as may be prescribed by law.
BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED, that the foregoing amendment be referred to the One
Hundred Fifteenth General Assembly and that this resolution proposing such amendment be
published in accordance with Article XI, Section 3 of the Constitution of Tennessee by posting
such amendment on the official website of the Secretary of State and on the official website of
the General Assembly.
BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED, that the Clerk of the Senate is directed to deliver a copy
of this resolution to the Secretary of State, with this final resolving clause being deleted from
such copies.
